1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:03,120
DOCTOR:
This little girl it's all about her.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,560
Who was she?

3
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:07,480
RORY: Doctor, what is happening to her?

4
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:09,240
Contractions.

5
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:11,440
-Contractions?
-She's going into lab our.

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:13,040
Breathe.

7
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:15,840
I needed enough information
to block the signal to the Flesh.

8
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:16,920
What signal?

9
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,200
The signal to you.

10
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:21,240
-Rory, I don't like this.
-Stand away from her, Rory.

11
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:23,200
We're coming for you, I swear.

12
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:29,160
And whatever happens, however hard,
however far, we will find you.

13
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:30,400
I'm right here.

14
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:32,800
No, you're not.

15
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:39,440
And you haven't been
for a long, long time.

16
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:41,960
(GASPS)

17
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,440
You're ready to pop, aren't you?

18
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:48,040
(SCREAMS)

19
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,280
AMY: I wish I could tell you
that you'll be loved.

20
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:05,960
That you'll be safe and cared for
and protected.

21
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:10,080
But this isn't a time for lies.

22
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:18,120
What you are going to be, Melody,

23
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,960
is very, very brave.

24
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,280
Two minutes.

25
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:27,000
But not as brave as they'll have to be,

26
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,320
because there's someone's coming.

27
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:32,200
I don't know where he is
or what he's doing

28
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:36,040
but trust me, he's on his way.

29
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:53,280
Intruder, level nine. Seal level nine.

30
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:57,000
There's a man
who's never going to let us down.

31
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:01,320
And not even an army can get in the way.

32
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,960
Leave her. Just you leave her.

33
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:12,800
(SOBBING) Please, leave her!

34
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,920
Please, leave her!

35
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:21,200
Intruder, level 11.
Seal levels 12, 13 and 14.

36
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,920
Intruder, level 75.

37
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,360
(CRYING)

38
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,720
He's the last of his kind.

39
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:34,040
He looks young but he's lived for
hundreds and hundreds of years.

40
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:39,760
And wherever they take you, Melody,
however scared you are,

41
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,000
I promise you,

42
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:45,560
you will never be alone.

43
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,720
(CRYING)

44
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,200
Because this man is your father.

45
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,840
Prepare to engage.

46
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:05,520
He has a name, but the people
of our world know him better...

47
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,440
...as the Last Centurion.

48
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,480
I have a message and a question.

49
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:19,000
A message from the Doctor
and a question from me.

50
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:22,560
Where is my wife?

51
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,920
Oh, don't give me those blank looks.

52
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:33,600
The Twelfth Cyber Legion
monitors this entire quadrant.

53
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,880
You hear everything.

54
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,560
So, you tell me what I need to know.

55
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,360
You tell me now and I'll be on my way.

56
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:47,640
What is the Doctor's message?

57
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,800
Would you like me
to repeat the question?

58
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:02,120
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

59
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,120
MAN 1: A whole cyber legion, though,

60
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,280
he just blew them all up
to make a point!

61
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,760
MAN 2: We're being paid
to fight him, not praise him.

62
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,800
Praising costs way more.

63
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:00,560
Level minus-23 transept.

64
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,680
Digger says he once
chased the Atraxi off a planet

65
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:08,480
then called them back for a scolding.

66
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:11,120
MAN 2: Fight him, not praise him.

67
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:13,760
WOMAN ON PA: Alert.
This base is on yellow alert.

68
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,600
This base is on yellow alert.

69
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,600
Is she sewing?

70
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:21,160
She's on her break,
she can do what she likes.

71
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,600
-Now, try again.
-(SIGHS)

72
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:26,960
That one.

73
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:29,920
No that's the psychic.
You got to look for the fractals.

74
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,840
Don't look bored, we're on yellow alert.

75
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,720
We've been on yellow alert
for three weeks.

76
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:41,320
WOMAN ON PA: Reminder.
Do not interact with Headless Monks

77
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,040
without divine permission.

78
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:46,480
Do not interact with Headless Monks
without divine permission.

79
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,400
We're not supposed to stare at them.

80
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,960
And if they think we're trying to see
under their hoods, they'll kill you.

81
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,080
On the spot.

82
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:55,440
Why are they called the Headless Monks?
They can't really be headless.

83
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:58,000
LORNA: They believe
the domain of faith is the heart

84
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,680
and the domain of doubt is the head.

85
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:02,360
They follow their hearts, that's all.

86
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:05,040
-You're Lorna Bucket, aren't you?
-Yep.

87
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:08,200
Hello, I'm the thin one.
This is my husband, he's the fat one.

88
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,200
Don't you have names?

89
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:14,400
We're the thin-fat, gay, married
Anglican Marines.

90
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,600
Why would we need names as well?

91
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,880
(MONKS CHANTING)

92
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:22,320
Oh, looks like I'm off.
Time for my conversion tutorial.

93
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,840
See you in a bit.

94
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,440
Do you have Lent?
'Cause I'm not good at giving things up.

95
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,160
Lorna Bucket.

96
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,880
You've had an encounter, haven't you?

97
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:37,080
-You've met him.
-I was just a kid.

98
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:39,560
But what's he like, the Doctor?

99
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,480
He said, "Run."

100
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,360
-Just "run"?
-He said it a lot.

101
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,040
And this was in the Gamma Forests, yeah?
Cause you're a Gamma girl, aren't you?

102
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,680
What are you doing here?
The Forests are heaven-neutral.

103
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,880
Yeah.

104
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:59,280
And 30 seconds of the Doctor is the only
thing that ever happened there.

105
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:04,520
Oh, this is nice. I like this.

106
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,880
I mean, quite a lot of red.

107
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:11,280
Hope it's not to hide the stains?
(LAUGHING)

108
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,520
What's in the little boxes?

109
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:19,360
WOMAN ON PA: Welcome, Applicant,
to the Order of the Headless.

110
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:23,280
It is traditional for visiting armies
of other faiths

111
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:27,280
to offer individuals for conversion
to our order.

112
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,280
You have been selected.

113
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,960
Are you ready

114
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,720
to make a donation?

115
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,240
So, what do you think?

116
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:43,920
If the Doctor's really coming here,
where is he?

117
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,640
He's the Doctor,
he could be anywhere in time and space.

118
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,080
Whoa!

119
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:58,640
Thank you, Parky.
I won't be needing you again tonight.

120
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,160
DRIVER: Yes, milady.

121
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:05,440
Oh, you're back early, ma'am.
Another case cracked, I assume?

122
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,920
Send a telegram to Inspector Abberline
of the Yard.

123
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,880
Jack The Ripper
has claimed his last victim.

124
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,360
(WHISPERING) How did you find him?

125
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,840
Stringy.

126
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,000
But tasty all the same.

127
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:23,360
-I shan't be needing dinner.
-Congratulations, ma'am.

128
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,720
However, um...

129
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,120
a matter has arisen in the drawing room.

130
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,000
It just appeared. What does it mean?

131
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,880
It means

132
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,880
a very old debt is to be repaid.

133
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:48,200
Pack the cases, Jenny,
we're going to need the swords.

134
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,240
(SHOUTING) Nurse.

135
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,400
Nurse!

136
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,320
Damn it, where's the nurse?

137
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,960
He needs help.

138
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,160
Madam President, I'm sorry,
but we have to go now.

139
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,920
Those things could be here any second.

140
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,520
Did somebody call for a nurse?

141
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,760
Will I be okay?

142
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:22,360
Of course you will, my boy,
you'll be up and around in no time.

143
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,480
And perhaps one day, you and I
shall meet on the field of battle

144
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,880
and I will destroy you
for the glory of the Sontaran Empire.

145
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,200
-Thanks, nurse.
-Pleasure.

146
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,480
(EXPLOSION)

147
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:40,720
Commander Strax,
I just have to ask, a Sontaran nurse?

148
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,840
I serve a penance to restore
the honour of my clone batch.

149
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:46,600
It is the greatest punishment
a Sontaran can endure.

150
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:50,160
-To help the weak and sick.
-Who came up with that one?

151
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,880
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

152
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:01,600
Tonight, though,
perhaps my penance is over.

153
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:07,000
Captain Harcourt, I hope someday
to meet you in the glory of battle,

154
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:10,080
where I shall crush the life
from your worthless human form.

155
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,000
Try and get some rest.

156
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,880
(KLAXONS SOUNDING)

157
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,880
Oh, turn it off,
I'm breaking in, not out.

158
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,840
This is River Song, back in her cell.

159
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,160
(KLAXONS STOP)

160
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,880
Oh, and I'll take breakfast
at the usual time.

161
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,360
Thank you.

162
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:43,320
Oh, are you boys dressing up
as Romans now?

163
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,160
I thought nobody read my memos.

164
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,880
Dr Song,

165
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,640
it's Rory.

166
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,240
Sorry, have we met yet?

167
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,720
The time streams,
I'm not quite sure where we are.

168
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,760
Yes. Yes, we've met.

169
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,240
Hello, Rory.

170
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,960
What's wrong?

171
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,280
(GASPS) It's my birthday.

172
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:17,120
The Doctor took me ice skating
on the River Thames in 1814,

173
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,000
the last of the great Frost Fairs.

174
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:22,200
He got Stevie Wonder to sing
for me under London Bridge.

175
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,880
Stevie Wonder sang in 18147

176
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:26,800
Yes, he did!
But you must never tell him.

177
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,800
I've come from the Doctor, too.

178
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:35,480
-Yes, but at a different point in time.
-Unless there's two of them.

179
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:38,840
Now, that's a whole different birthday.

180
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,840
He needs you.

181
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,040
Demon's Run.

182
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
How...

183
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,200
How did you know?

184
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,280
I'm from his future. I always know.

185
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,560
Why on earth are you wearing that?

186
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,640
-The Doctor's idea.
-Of course.

187
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,800
His rules of engagement.

188
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,760
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

189
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,760
-Look ridiculous.
-Have you considered heels?

190
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:09,200
They've taken Amy. And our baby.

191
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,640
The Doctor's getting
some people together.

192
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,920
We're going after her,
but he needs you too.

193
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,640
I can't.

194
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,640
Not yet, anyway.

195
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,400
I'm sorry?

196
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,600
This is the battle of Demon's Run,

197
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,200
the Doctor's darkest hour.

198
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:36,640
He'll rise higher than ever before
and then fall so much further.

199
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,760
And I can't be with him
till the very end.

200
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,160
Why not?

201
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,360
Because this is it.

202
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:55,360
This is the day he finds out who I am.

203
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,240
(SIGHS)

204
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,760
Goodbye.

205
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:18,840
You appear to be closing down, Dorium.

206
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,520
What have you heard?

207
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:25,280
That you pricked the side
of a mighty beast, Madam Kovarian,

208
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,400
and entirely failed to run.

209
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:33,000
(SIGHS) I admire your courage.
I should like to admire it from afar.

210
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,640
We've been waiting a month.
He's done nothing.

211
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,200
Do you really think so?

212
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:41,640
There are people all over this galaxy
that owe that man a debt.

213
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,800
By now, a few of them
will have found a blue box

214
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,760
waiting for them on their doorstep.
Poor devils.

215
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,600
You think he's raising an army?

216
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,040
You think he isn't?

217
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:54,920
If that man is finally collecting
on his debts, God help you.

218
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,360
And God help his debtors.

219
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,560
Why?

220
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,160
Colonel Manton,

221
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,680
all those stories
you've heard about him,

222
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,800
they're not stories, they're true.

223
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,440
(LAUGHING) Really.

224
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,880
You're not telling me
you don't know what's coming?

225
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,960
-We're wasting our time here.
-Agreed.

226
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,680
The asteroid,

227
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,560
where you've made your base,

228
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,320
do you know
why they call it Demon's Run?

229
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:23,160
How do you know
the location of our base?

230
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:26,720
(SIGHS) You're with the Headless Monks,
they're old customers of mine.

231
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,680
It's just some old saying.

232
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:31,440
A very old saying. The oldest.

233
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:35,440
"Demons run
when a good man goes to war."

234
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,600
(LAUGHING)

235
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,720
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

236
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:55,000
No! No, no, please! Not me.

237
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,800
You don't need me.
Why would you need me?

238
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:02,160
I'm old, I'm fat, I'm blue.

239
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:05,000
You can't need me!

240
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,120
He is not the Devil.

241
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:12,440
He's not a god.

242
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:18,160
He's not a goblin or a phantom
or a trickster.

243
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,520
The Doctor is a living, breathing man.

244
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:27,440
And as I look around this room,
I know one thing,

245
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,680
we're sure as hell going to fix that.

246
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,280
ALL: Yes!

247
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:37,640
Yes/

248
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:41,080
(DOOR CLOSES)

249
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:45,200
Sorry.

250
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,240
I... I shouldn't be here,
I'm meant to be at the thing.

251
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,200
I brought you something.

252
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:58,320
Your child's name,
in the language of my people.

253
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:03,800
It's a prayer leaf, and we believe
if you keep this with you,

254
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,200
your child will always come home to you.

255
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:08,240
Can I borrow your gun?

256
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,600
Why?

257
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:13,880
'Cause I've got a feeling
you're going to keep talking.

258
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,360
(CROWD CHEERING)

259
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,440
They're talking like he's famous.

260
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:27,080
The Doctor isn't famous.

261
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:29,520
He meets a lot of people.

262
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,800
Some of them remember.

263
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,720
He's sort of like a...

264
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:36,960
I don't know.

265
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,320
-A dark legend.
-Dark.

266
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,200
-Have you met him?
-Yeah.

267
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,480
But I was just a little girl then.

268
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:50,440
So was I.

269
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,680
You've been with him a long time, then?

270
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,720
No.

271
00:16:57,760 --> 00:16:58,920
He came back for me.

272
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,520
You must be very special.

273
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:09,400
Hey,

274
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,640
you can wait a long time for the Doctor
but he's worth it, okay?

275
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:17,920
Thing is, he's coming,
no question about it.

276
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,960
Just you make sure you're on
the right side when he gets here.

277
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,200
Not for my sake, for yours.

278
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,880
Thank you.

279
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:43,520
On this day, in this place,
the Doctor will fall.

280
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,080
ALL: (SHOUTING) Hurrah!

281
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:48,600
The man who talks, the man who reasons,

282
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:52,360
the man who lies
will meet the perfect answer.

283
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,600
ALL: Hurrah!

284
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:58,760
Some of you have wondered
why we have allied ourselves

285
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,800
with the Headless Monks.

286
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:05,920
Perhaps you should have wondered
why we call them "headless".

287
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:14,040
It's time you knew what these guys
have sacrificed for faith.

288
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:20,640
As you all know,
it is a level one heresy,

289
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:25,160
punishable by death,
to lower the hood of a Headless Monk.

290
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:31,600
But by the divine grant
of the Papal Mainframe herself,

291
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:37,400
on this one and only occasion,
I can show you the truth.

292
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:43,440
Because these guys never can be...

293
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,120
persuaded.

294
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,520
They never can be...

295
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,400
afraid.

296
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:01,760
And they can never ever be...

297
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:02,960
(ALL GASPING)

298
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:05,000
Surprised.

299
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:13,520
(LAUGHS) Hello everyone, guess who?

300
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:16,800
Please, point a gun at me,
if it helps you relax.

301
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,160
(COCKING GUNS)

302
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:23,880
You're only human.

303
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:32,160
Go on, resist, I am ever so hungry.

304
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:35,080
Now, dear,
which button controls the lights?

305
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:38,680
Doctor, you will come with me right now.

306
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,600
Three minutes, 40 seconds.

307
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:45,120
Amelia Pond! Get your coat!

308
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,280
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

309
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:48,800
(ALL MUMBLING)

310
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,800
-DOCTOR: I'm not a phantom.
-Doctor?

311
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,360
I'm not a trickster.

312
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,120
-Doctor?
-I'm a Monk.

313
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,200
-Doctor, show yourself.
-It's him!

314
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,760
He's here.

315
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,360
It's him!

316
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,520
(GUNSHOT)

317
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:21,320
Weapons down. Do not fire!

318
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,880
No!

319
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,440
Follow me.

320
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:34,040
Doctor? Doctor!

321
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:38,760
-Clever, isn't he?
-And rather attractive.

322
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,920
You do realise he's a man,
don't you, ma'am?

323
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,440
-Mammals, they all look alike.
-Thank you.

324
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:48,200
Do not fire. Nobody discharge
their weapon in this room.

325
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,280
Nobody.

326
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:51,920
Do not fire.

327
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:57,880
Was I being insensitive again, dear?
I don't know why you put up with me.

328
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,560
MANTON: Stop, wait.

329
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,360
Listen to me.

330
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:10,600
I'm disarming my weapon pack.

331
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,920
Monks, I do this in good faith.

332
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,520
I am now unarmed.

333
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,720
(MURMURING)

334
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:27,200
All of you discharge you weapon packs.

335
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:31,040
The Doctor is trying
to make fools of us.

336
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,320
We are soldiers of God.

337
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,040
We are not fools.

338
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,280
We are not fools.

339
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,800
We are not fools.

340
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,280
We are not fools.

341
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,880
We are not fools.

342
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:49,920
COLONEL MANTON: We are not fools.

343
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,520
We are not fools.

344
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,920
We are not fools.

345
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,160
We're not fools.

346
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:59,840
-Colonel Manton is regaining control.
-Where has the Doctor gone?

347
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:12,240
ALL: We are not fools.

348
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:14,600
We are not fools.

349
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:17,560
We are not fools!

350
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:24,640
(HISSING)

351
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,240
(GROWLING)

352
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:43,440
This space is now under our command.

353
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:45,160
I have a fleet out there.

354
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:48,920
If Demon's Run goes down,
there's an automatic distress call.

355
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,880
DOCTOR: Not if we knock out
your communications array.

356
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,880
And you've got incoming.

357
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:56,840
Danny Boy to the Doctor,
Danny Boy to the Doctor.

358
00:22:56,920 --> 00:22:59,040
Give 'em hell, Danny Boy.

359
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,400
(MIMICKING PLANE)

360
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,080
(MIMICKING GUNFIRE)

361
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:13,560
I need to get off this station now.

362
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,840
Bring me the child.

363
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,040
(ALARMS SOUNDING)

364
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,400
DANNY BOY: Target destroyed.

365
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:20,200
(LAUGHING)

366
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,600
Don't slump, it's bad for your spine.

367
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,160
(MELODY CRYING)

368
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,040
KOVARIAN:
Get back in there with the rest of them.

369
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:38,760
Remember,
the Doctor must think he's winning

370
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,800
right until the trap closes.

371
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,880
I'll take my ship from here.

372
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:46,760
(MELODY CRYING)

373
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:50,680
AUTOMATED VOICE: Air lock engaged.
Shuttle ready for boarding.

374
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:52,200
No.

375
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:56,400
I have a crew of 20.

376
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:59,000
How do you expect
to gain control of my ship?

377
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,280
(SMIRKS)

378
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:03,320
The ship is ours, milady.

379
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:09,560
All airlocks sealed.
Resistance neutralised.

380
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,960
DOCTOR: Sorry, Colonel Manton, I lied.

381
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,600
Three minutes 42 seconds.

382
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:20,520
Colonel Manton, you will give the order
for your men to withdraw.

383
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:25,080
No, Colonel Manton,
I want you to tell your men to run away.

384
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,200
What?

385
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,680
Those words, "Run away."

386
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,800
I want you to be famous
for those exact words.

387
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,480
I want people to call you
Colonel Runaway.

388
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,400
I want children
laughing outside your door

389
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,640
'cause they've found the house
of Colonel Runaway.

390
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,720
And when people come to you

391
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:43,920
and ask if trying to get to me
through the people I love...

392
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,520
(HISSING)

393
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,000
...Is in any way a good idea,

394
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:54,880
I want you to tell them your name.

395
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,400
Look, I'm angry, that's new.

396
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,520
I'm really not sure
what's going to happen now.

397
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:05,160
KOVARIAN: The anger of a good man
is not a problem.

398
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,760
Good men have too many rules.

399
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:17,320
Good men don't need rules.

400
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:23,600
Today is not the day
to find out why I have so many.

401
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,600
-Hmm?
-Give the order.

402
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:38,680
Give the order, Colonel Runaway.

403
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:40,440
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

404
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,560
Who's that? Who's there?
You watch it, because I am armed

405
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:48,680
and really dangerous and cross.

406
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,880
RORY: Yeah, like I don't know that.

407
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:54,640
Rory? Rory, is that you?

408
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,440
Yeah, it's me.

409
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,760
Look, hang on a minute.

410
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,960
They took her.

411
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,920
Rory, they took our baby away.

412
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:15,600
Now, Mrs Williams,
that is never ever going to happen.

413
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,120
(MELODY COOING)

414
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,000
Oh, my God.

415
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,160
Where's she been?
What have they done to her?

416
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:35,320
She's fine. Amy, she's fine, I checked.

417
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,240
She's beautiful.

418
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:43,400
Oh, God, I was going to be cool.

419
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:46,680
-I wanted to be cool and look at me.
-You're okay.

420
00:26:47,320 --> 00:26:50,280
A crying Roman with a baby.
Definitely cool.

421
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,480
Come here, you.

422
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:59,600
Ew, kissing and crying.
I'll... I'll be back in a bit.

423
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:03,720
Oi, you. Get in here, now.

424
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:10,440
My daughter.

425
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:15,080
-What do you think?
-Hello. Hello, uh...

426
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:17,440
-...baby.
-Uh, Melody.

427
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,680
Melody? Hello, Melody Pond.

428
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:22,400
-Melody Williams.
-Is a geography teacher.

429
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,640
Melody Pond is a superhero.

430
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:26,120
(DOCTOR SNIFFING)

431
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,840
Well, yes,
I suppose she does smell nice.

432
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,600
Never really sniffed a...

433
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:32,360
Maybe I should give it a go.
Amelia Pond, come here.

434
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:33,520
Doctor.

435
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,800
Sorry we were so long. (SNIFFS) Ah.

436
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:40,280
It's okay. I knew you were coming.
Both of you, my boys.

437
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,480
(MELODY SQUEALS)

438
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:45,280
It's okay. She's still all yours
and really you should call her Mummy.

439
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:47,880
-Not Big Milk Thing.
-(MELODY COOS)

440
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:50,720
-Okay, what are you doing?
-I speak baby.

441
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,240
No, you don't.

442
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,800
I speak everything.

443
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,960
Don't I, Melody Pond?

444
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,880
No, it's not. It's cool.

445
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:02,080
(LAUGHING)

446
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,720
Doctor, take a look, they're leaving.

447
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:08,720
Demon's Run is ours
without a drop of blood spilled.

448
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,520
My friend, you have never risen higher.

449
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,440
-(SHUSHING)
-Hey, what's wrong?

450
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:24,280
She doesn't like the Tardis noise.
I asked him to turn something off,

451
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:25,880
but it was all,
"But I don't want to punch a hole

452
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,720
"in the space-time continuum."”

453
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:31,840
Rory, the Judoon have escorted
the clerics out of the quadrant.

454
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,840
Spitfires have returned
to their own time.

455
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,760
Captain Avery and his men are going...
Is she all right?

456
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:37,880
Yeah, she's just crying.

457
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,840
Give her to me, human fools,
she needs changing.

458
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:42,640
I just changed her.
I think she might need a feed.

459
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:46,080
A feed?
Of course, I'll take care of everything.

460
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:49,040
Uh, I really don't think
you will, actually.

461
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:52,000
I have gene-spliced myself
for all nursing duties.

462
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:55,040
I can produce magnificent quantities
of lactic fluid.

463
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:58,160
She's not hungry, she's tired.

464
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:00,960
Sorry, Melody,
they're just not listening.

465
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:03,800
What's this? Melody?

466
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,480
Very pretty, according to your daughter.

467
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:07,880
-It's, uh...
-It's a cot.

468
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:10,440
-No flies on the Roman.
-(LAUGHS)

469
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:13,720
Give her here.
Hey, here we go. Oh, hello.

470
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:16,280
RORY: But where would you get a cot?

471
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:18,560
It's old. Really old.

472
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:22,720
Doctor, um, do you have children?

473
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,040
No.

474
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:27,280
Have you ever had children?

475
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,280
(COOING)

476
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,880
No, no, it's real, it's my hair.

477
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:34,680
(LAUGHS) Who slept in here?

478
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:36,400
VASTRA: Doctor, we need you
in the main control room.

479
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,480
DOCTOR: Be right there.

480
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:39,840
Things to do. I've still got to work out
what this base is for.

481
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:42,440
We can't leave till we know.

482
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,920
Uh, but this is where I was.

483
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:49,320
The whole time I thought I was
on the Tardis, I was really here.

484
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:53,200
Ah, Centurion, permission to hug?

485
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:57,400
-Be aware, I do have a sword.
-At all times.

486
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:06,080
You were on the Tardis, too,
your heart and mind, soul.

487
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:09,480
But physically, yes,
you were still in this place.

488
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:11,320
And when I saw that face looking
through the hatch,

489
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:12,600
that woman looking at me?

490
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:13,720
Reality bleeding through.

491
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:15,320
They must've taken you
quite a while back,

492
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:17,200
just before America.

493
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:20,080
That's probably enough hugging now.

494
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:25,240
So, her flesh avatar was
with us all that time?

495
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:28,080
But that means they were projecting a
control signal right into the Tardis,

496
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,240
-wherever we were in time and space.
-Yeah, they're very clever.

497
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:31,880
-Who are?
-Whoever wants our baby.

498
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,320
-Why did they want her?
-Exactly.

499
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:37,120
Is there anything you're not telling us?

500
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:39,960
You knew Amy wasn't real,
you never said.

501
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:42,200
Well, I couldn't be sure
they weren't listening.

502
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,120
But you always hold out on us,
please, not this time.

503
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:48,440
Doctor, it's our baby.
Tell us something. One little thing.

504
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:50,800
It's mine.

505
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,760
-What is?
-Cot. It's my cot.

506
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,560
I slept in there.

507
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:04,120
Oh, my God.
It's the Doctor's first stars.

508
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:05,800
(GIGGLES)

509
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,360
She's...

510
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:13,040
STRAX: Drop your weapons!
State your rank and intent.

511
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:15,800
I found it listening at the door.

512
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:17,520
You've hacked into their software, then?

513
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:20,400
-I believe I sold it to them.
-Ooh. So what have we learned?

514
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,800
That anger is always
the shortest distance to a mistake.

515
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:26,200
-I'm sorry?
-The words of an old friend,

516
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:29,400
who once found me
in the London Underground

517
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:33,200
attempting to avenge my sisters
on perfectly innocent tunnel diggers.

518
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,640
Well, you were very cross at the time.

519
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:39,280
As you were today, old friend.
Point taken, I hope.

520
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:43,600
Now, I have a question. A simple one.
Is Melody human?

521
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,520
Sorry, what? (LAUGHS)

522
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,960
Of course she is. Completely human.

523
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,720
What are you talking about?

524
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,520
They've been scanning her
since she was born.

525
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:55,640
And I think they found
what they were looking for.

526
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:58,520
-Human DNA.
-Look closer.

527
00:31:58,600 --> 00:31:59,960
Human plus.

528
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:04,120
Specifically, human plus Time Lord.

529
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:08,880
But I heard her talking. This is a trap.

530
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:10,400
Why would I lie to you?

531
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:12,400
Well, you might want
to take a look at your uniform.

532
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:15,520
The only reason I joined the clerics
was so I could meet the Doctor again.

533
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:18,960
You wanted to meet him
so you joined an army to fight him?

534
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:20,920
Well, how else
do you meet a great warrior?

535
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,560
-He's not a warrior.
-Then why is he called the Doctor?

536
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,200
It's starting. Please listen to me!

537
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:37,000
But she's human.
She's Amy and Rory's daughter.

538
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,680
You've told me about your people.

539
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:42,480
They became what they did through
prolonged exposure to the time vortex.

540
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,440
The untempered schism.

541
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:47,720
Over billions of years.
It didn't just happen.

542
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:50,960
So, how close is she...
Could she even regenerate?

543
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:54,960
No! No. I don't think so.

544
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,520
You don't sound so sure.

545
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,120
Because I don't understand
how this happened.

546
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,040
Which leads me to ask,
when did it happen?

547
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:03,080
When?

548
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,760
I am trying to be delicate.
I know how you can blush.

549
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,200
(CHUCKLES)

550
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,520
When did this baby...

551
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,880
begin?

552
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,240
-Oh, you mean...
-Quite.

553
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:21,000
Well, how would I know?
That's all humany private stuff.

554
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:23,560
It just sort of goes on.
They don't put up a balloon or anything.

555
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:27,240
Well, could the child have begun
on the Tardis, in flight, in the vortex?

556
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:30,120
No! No! Impossible.

557
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,880
It's all running about,
sexy fish vampires

558
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,160
and blowing up stuff.

559
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:36,800
And Rory wasn't even there
at the beginning. Then he was dead.

560
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:39,800
Then he didn't exist.
Then he was plastic.

561
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:42,000
Then I had to reboot the whole universe.
Long story.

562
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,320
So, technically,

563
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,840
the first time they were on the Tardis
together in this version of reality

564
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:46,960
was on their...

565
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:49,720
-On their what?
-Hmm?

566
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:52,360
On their wedding night.

567
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,680
Confirmed.

568
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:57,720
No life forms registering on this base
except us and the Silurians.

569
00:33:57,800 --> 00:34:00,240
The Headless Monks aren't alive.

570
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,120
They don't register as life forms.

571
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,920
(LOW CHANTING)

572
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:11,640
It doesn't make sense. You can't
just cook yourself a Time Lord.

573
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:12,760
Of course not.

574
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:15,040
(SIGHING)
But you gave them one hell of a start

575
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:17,360
and they've been working very hard
ever since.

576
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:20,280
And yet they gave in so easily.
Does this not bother anyone else?

577
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:23,120
Amy, she worried that the baby
would have a time head, she said that...

578
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:25,320
Only you would ignore
the instincts of a mother.

579
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,280
Or the instincts of a coward.

580
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:29,240
This is too easy.
There's something wrong.

581
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,320
Why even do it?

582
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:32,360
Even if you could get your hands
on a brand new Time Lord, what for?

583
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,520
-A weapon?
-Why would a Time Lord be a weapon?

584
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:38,040
Well, they've seen you.

585
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:40,880
Me?

586
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:47,480
VASTRA: Mr Maldavar, you are right.
This was too easy.

587
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:49,360
We should get back to the others.

588
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:53,040
(SOFTLY) Me.

589
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:06,080
I'd say she's human,
going by the life support software.

590
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:07,760
She climbed out of the suit.

591
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:11,760
Like, she forced her way out.
She must be incredibly strong.

592
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:13,800
KOVARIAN: I see you accessed our files.

593
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,840
Do you understand yet?

594
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:19,480
Oh, don't worry. I'm a long way away.

595
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:22,080
But I like to keep tabs on you.

596
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:25,400
The child, then. What do you think?

597
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,440
-What is she?
-Hope.

598
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:32,880
Hope in this endless, bitter war.

599
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:35,840
What war? Against who?

600
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:39,880
Against you, Doctor.

601
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:45,600
(CHANTING)

602
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:52,160
What's that?

603
00:35:58,840 --> 00:35:59,840
(GASPS)

604
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,920
-Force field.
-(THUDDING)

605
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:05,160
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

606
00:36:05,240 --> 00:36:07,160
(THUDDING CONTINUES)

607
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:08,760
LORNA: And those are the doors.

608
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:10,520
Locking.

609
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:18,080
Apparently we're not leaving.

610
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:20,560
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

611
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:24,800
-Is that the monks?
-Oh, dear God!

612
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:26,120
That's the attack prayer.

613
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,600
RORY: Quick, come with me.

614
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:28,800
VASTRA: Commander Strax.

615
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:31,760
STRAX: I'm trying to seal off this area
of the lighting grid.

616
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:34,560
This is where we'll make our stand.

617
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:37,280
Clear lines of sight on all approaches.

618
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,520
(CHANTING)

619
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:41,680
Rory, no offence to the others,

620
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:44,000
but you'll let them all die first, okay?

621
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:45,240
You're so Scottish.

622
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,760
(LAUGHS)

623
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,080
VASTRA: Centurion, you're needed!

624
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:05,040
There should be some plasma pistols
somewhere. They left everything.

625
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,320
STRAX: Then find them, boy!

626
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:09,320
-She's definitely a girl.
-Oh, stop it!

627
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:11,920
We don't have to fight them.

628
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:15,840
I'm friends to the monks. They know me.

629
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:18,640
Yeah, and they know
you just sold them out to the Doctor.

630
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:23,080
Oh, they'll understand. It's only me.
Only silly old me.

631
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:26,320
You understand, don't you?

632
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,320
VASTRA: Mr Maldavar, get back here.

633
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,280
-STRAX: Arm yourself, fool.
-Dorium!

634
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:32,360
(MONKS CHANTING URGENTLY)

635
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:34,920
(SWORD STABBING, THUD)

636
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,600
VASTRA: Mr Maldavar?

637
00:37:37,240 --> 00:37:38,280
Dorium?

638
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,120
VASTRA: The child.

639
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,880
At all costs, protect the child.

640
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,920
The child is not a weapon!

641
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:56,200
Oh, give us time. She can be.

642
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,680
She will be.

643
00:37:57,760 --> 00:37:59,800
Except you've already lost her,
and I swear

644
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,960
I will never let you
anywhere near her again.

645
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:06,040
(LAUGHS) Oh, Doctor,
fooling you once was a joy

646
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:09,280
but fooling you twice the same way?

647
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,880
It's a privilege.

648
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,520
Amy. Amy!

649
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,120
(GUNFIRE, MELODY CRYING)

650
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,240
(STRAX YELLING)

651
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:35,000
RIVER:
Demons run when a good man goes to war.

652
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:40,040
Night will fall and drown the sun
when a good man goes to war.

653
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:43,080
Friendship dies and true love lies,

654
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:46,400
night will fall and the dark will rise

655
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:48,600
when a good man goes to war.

656
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,000
Amy!

657
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:53,440
RIVER: Demons run but count the cost.

658
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:56,360
-The battle's won but the child is lost.
-Amy!

659
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:59,280
Wakey wakey.

660
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:00,600
Amy!

661
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:02,840
(GASPS)

662
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:07,120
(SOFTLY) Rory?

663
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:10,080
(SCREAMING) Rory! Rory!

664
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,360
(WHIMPERING)

665
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:15,000
Amy, she's not real.

666
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:17,040
Melody, she's a flesh avatar.

667
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:18,760
Amy!

668
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,640
Amy!

669
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:24,760
(SOFTLY) Amy?

670
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:32,120
Yeah, we know.

671
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,560
(STRAX GROANING)

672
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,520
STRAX: It's strange.

673
00:39:44,680 --> 00:39:47,600
I have often dreamed of dying in combat.

674
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:52,080
I'm not enjoying it
as much as I had hoped.

675
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,600
RORY: Come on, Strax.

676
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,480
-Don't give up.
-It's all right.

677
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:58,560
I've had a good life.

678
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,360
I'm nearly 12.

679
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:04,120
Listen to me.

680
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:07,040
You'll be back on your feet in no time.
You're a warrior.

681
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:08,480
(SIGHING)

682
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:10,320
Rory,

683
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:14,440
I'm a nurse.

684
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,760
(COUGHING WEAKLY)

685
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:36,400
So they took her anyway.

686
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:39,240
All this was for nothing.

687
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,520
I am so...

688
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,120
sorry.

689
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:50,120
Amy, it's not his fault.

690
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,640
I know. I know.

691
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:03,560
Doctor, there's someone
who wants to speak to you.

692
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:06,680
He name is Lorna. She came to warn us.

693
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:16,840
(SIGHING)

694
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:22,120
Hey. Hello.

695
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,520
Doctor.

696
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,040
You helped my friends.

697
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,000
Thank you.

698
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:33,960
I met you once.

699
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:38,400
In the Gamma Forests.

700
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,560
You don't remember me.

701
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,120
Hey, of course I remember.

702
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:48,200
I remember everyone.

703
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:52,720
Hey. We ran.

704
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,040
You and me.

705
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,560
Didn't we run, Lorna?

706
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:14,560
Who was she?

707
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:17,320
I don't know but she was very brave.

708
00:42:20,520 --> 00:42:21,680
They're always brave.

709
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:26,760
They're always brave.

710
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:29,680
So, what now?

711
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:32,320
They'd almost certainly
have taken her to Earth,

712
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:34,480
raised her in the correct environment.

713
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:38,120
Yes, they did.
And it's already too late.

714
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:39,680
You're giving up? You never do that.

715
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,120
Yeah, and don't you sometimes
wish I did?

716
00:42:41,520 --> 00:42:42,880
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

717
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:48,080
RIVER: Well, then, soldier,
how goes the day?

718
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:56,920
Where the hell have you been?

719
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:58,720
Every time you have asked,
I have been there.

720
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:00,600
Where the hell were you today?

721
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:04,640
-I couldn't have prevented this.
-You could have tried.

722
00:43:04,720 --> 00:43:06,400
And so, my love, could you.

723
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:10,440
I know you're not all right.

724
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,880
But hold tight, Amy,
because you're going to be.

725
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:17,440
You think I wanted this?
I didn't do this.

726
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:19,640
This... This wasn't me!

727
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:22,680
This was exactly you.
All this. ALI of it.

728
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:25,160
You make them so afraid.

729
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:29,280
When you began all those years ago,
sailing off to see the universe,

730
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:31,200
did you ever think you'd become this?

731
00:43:32,320 --> 00:43:35,440
The man who can turn an army around
at the mention of his name.

732
00:43:36,760 --> 00:43:37,960
Doctor.

733
00:43:38,880 --> 00:43:43,120
The word for "healer" and "wise man"
throughout the universe.

734
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,960
We get that word from you, you know.

735
00:43:46,960 --> 00:43:51,600
But if you carry on the way you are,
what might that word come to mean?

736
00:43:54,280 --> 00:43:56,600
To the people of the Gamma Forests

737
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:59,880
the word "doctor”
means "mighty warrior".

738
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:03,040
How far you've come.

739
00:44:05,120 --> 00:44:07,280
And now they've taken a child.

740
00:44:07,360 --> 00:44:09,240
The child of your best friends.

741
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:14,480
And they're going to turn her
into a weapon just to bring you down.

742
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:16,440
And all this, my love,

743
00:44:17,520 --> 00:44:18,840
in fear of you.

744
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:32,800
Who are you?

745
00:44:35,360 --> 00:44:37,280
Oh, look, your cot.
Haven't seen that in a very long while.

746
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:39,920
No. No, you tell me. You tell me

747
00:44:40,400 --> 00:44:41,640
who you are.

748
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:47,280
I am telling you.

749
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,400
Can't you read?

750
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,200
Hello.

751
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:18,440
Hello.

752
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:20,200
(LAUGHS)

753
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:24,520
-(GIGGLING) But that means...
-I'm afraid it does.

754
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:30,120
Ooh. But you and I, we-we-we, uh...

755
00:45:30,600 --> 00:45:32,280
-Yes.
-(LAUGHS)

756
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:34,880
Ooh.

757
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:40,000
How do I look?

758
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,000
Amazing.

759
00:45:43,080 --> 00:45:45,000
-I'd better be.
-Yes, you'd better be.

760
00:45:45,080 --> 00:45:46,520
-Vastra and Jenny, till the next time.
-Doctor.

761
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:48,360
Rory and Amy,
I know where to find your daughter

762
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:50,400
and on my life, she will be safe.

763
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:51,840
River, get them all home.

764
00:45:51,920 --> 00:45:54,880
-Doctor?
-Look, where are you going?

765
00:45:55,720 --> 00:45:56,800
No.

766
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:00,280
(LAUGHS)

767
00:46:02,480 --> 00:46:03,600
(WHOOSHING)

768
00:46:17,160 --> 00:46:19,000
Where is he going?
What did you tell him?

769
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:21,720
Amy, you have to stay calm.

770
00:46:24,080 --> 00:46:25,920
Tell me what you told the Doctor.

771
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:27,400
RORY: Amy, no. Stop it.

772
00:46:27,480 --> 00:46:29,360
It's okay, Rory. She's fine. She's good.

773
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:31,560
It's the Tardis translation matrix.

774
00:46:31,640 --> 00:46:34,560
It takes a while to kick in
with the written word.

775
00:46:34,640 --> 00:46:35,880
You have to concentrate.

776
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:42,000
I still can't read it.

777
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:45,080
It's because it's Gallifreyan
and doesn't translate.

778
00:46:49,960 --> 00:46:51,040
But this will.

779
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,960
It's your daughter's name
in the language of the Forest.

780
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:58,960
I know my daughter's name.

781
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:02,080
Except they don't have
a word for "pond”

782
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:04,760
because the only water in the Forest
is the river.

783
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:08,200
The Doctor will find your daughter

784
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:10,600
and he will care for her,
whatever it takes.

785
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:12,920
And I know that.

786
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:24,480
It's me.

787
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:27,920
I'm Melody.

788
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:31,240
I'm your daughter.

